{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Percent-Encoding and Decoding","role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"WebURL"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncoding","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Encode Data for a URL, or Decode Data from a URL.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Percent-Encoding Sets","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/formEncoding"]},{"title":"Encoding and Decoding Lazily","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentEncoded","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecoded","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions"]}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"What is Percent-Encoding?","anchor":"What-is-Percent-Encoding","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because URLs are a string format, certain characters may have special meaning depending on their position:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\/\""},{"type":"text","text":" in the path is used to separate the path’s segments, and the first "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"?\""},{"type":"text","text":" in the URL"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"marks the start of the query section. This poses an interesting question:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"What if I have a path component that contains a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"literal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" forward-slash?"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC\/DC\" ","\/\/                                 ^","\/\/            \"AC\/DC\" should be a single component!"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When these situations occur, we need to encode (or “escape”) the slash in our path component,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so it won’t be confused with the path delimiters. URLs use a form of encoding called ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"percent-encoding","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"because it encodes binary data using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"%XX\""},{"text":" strings, where ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XX"},{"text":" is a hexadecimal byte value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the ASCII forward-slash character, the byte value is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2F"},{"type":"text","text":", so the URL shown above would become:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","\/\/                                 ^^^ 😌"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Percent-encoding is particularly important when building strings for URL components at runtime, because it means that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"even ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"\/\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"?\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" characters in user input won’t be confused with path delimiters or other characters with special","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"meaning to the URL. Additionally, since percent-encoding always produces an ASCII string, we can use it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to encode Unicode text in URLs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func urlForProfile(_ username: String) -> WebURL {","  var url  = WebURL(\"https:\/\/example.com\/\")!  ","  url.path = \"\/accounts\/\" + username.percentEncoded(using: .urlComponentSet) + \"\/profile\"","  return url","}","","urlForProfile(\"BakerAli88\") ","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/BakerAli88\/profile\"","urlForProfile(\"AC\/DC??\")","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/AC%2FDC%3F%3F\/profile\"                             ","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^","urlForProfile(\"Günther\")    ","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/G%C3%BCnther\/profile\"                            ","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^","urlForProfile(\"🦆\")","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/%F0%9F%A6%86\/profile\"","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since URL components are percent-encoded, their contents must be recovered by decoding.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let url = WebURL(\"https:\/\/%F0%9F%A6%86@example.com\/\")!","url.username                  \/\/ \"%F0%9F%A6%86\" - Who's that?","url.username.percentDecoded() \/\/ \"🦆\" - Oh..."],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Remember - percent encoding exists so that URL components have an unambiguous structure.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you decode a component’s value too early or too many times, you may introduce bugs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The following example demonstrates this with two approaches to split a path string in to its components.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let url = urlForBand(\"AC\/DC\") ","\/\/ \"https:\/\/example.com\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"                              ","\/\/                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^","","\/\/ The Right Way: Split, then decode each component.","let rawPath = url.path \/\/ \"\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","let rawPathComponents = rawPath.split(\"\/\").map { $0.percentDecoded() }","\/\/ ✅ [\"bands\", \"AC\/DC\"]","","\/\/ The Wrong Way: Decode the entire path, then split.","let decodedPath = url.path.percentDecoded() \/\/ \"\/bands\/AC\/DC\"","let decodedPathComponents = decodedPath.split(\"\/\")","\/\/ ❌ [\"bands\", \"AC\", \"DC\"]"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Working with percent-encoded path strings can be tricky. We recommend leaving it to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL\/pathComponents-swift.property","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" view wherever possible."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"tip","type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Data is encoded using a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet","type":"reference"},{"text":" that informs the encoder which characters are allowed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the resulting string. The URL Standard defines some encode-sets, and you can define your own.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Extensions to Standard Library Types","anchor":"Extensions-to-Standard-Library-Types","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"WebURL provides a number of extensions to standard library types to aid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in encoding or decoding percent-encoded data."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Encoding Text or Binary Data","anchor":"Encoding-Text-or-Binary-Data","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"String.percentEncoded(using: PercentEncodeSet) -> String","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Collection.percentEncodedString(using: PercentEncodeSet) -> String","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To percent-encode a String, call the ","type":"text"},{"code":".percentEncoded(using:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function and specify an encode-set to use.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is usually a good choice for arbitrary strings:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it includes all URL special characters, and encodes some additional characters to match the JavaScript function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"encodeURIComponent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you have binary data, you can call the ","type":"text"},{"code":".percentEncodedString(using:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function, which is available","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on all collections of bytes, to produce a percent-encoded ASCII string of its contents.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\"AC\/DC\".percentEncoded(using: .urlComponentSet)","\/\/ \"AC%2FDC\"","Data(...).percentEncodedString(using: .urlComponentSet)","\/\/ \"%BAt_%E0%11%22...\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"text":"Decoding Strings to Text or Binary Data","anchor":"Decoding-Strings-to-Text-or-Binary-Data","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"String.percentDecoded() -> String","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String.percentDecodedBytesArray() -> [UInt8]"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To decode a String containing percent-encoding, call the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentDecoded()"},{"text":" function, which decodes the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string to bytes and interprets them as Unicode text. If the decoded bytes do not contain Unicode text,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentDecodedBytesArray()"},{"text":" to retrieve the bytes as binary data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\"AC%2FDC\".percentDecoded()","\/\/ \"AC\/DC\"","\"%BAt_%E0%11%22\".percentDecodedBytesArray()","\/\/ [186, 116, 95, 224, 17, 34, ...]"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"text":"Encoding and Decoding Lazily","anchor":"Encoding-and-Decoding-Lazily","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For certain algorithms, it can be useful to percent-encode binary data, or to read decoded binary data, lazily.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"WebURL adds ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentEncoded(using:)"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentDecoded()"},{"text":" functions to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LazyCollection"},{"text":", each returning view objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which encode and decode data on-demand.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Creating or Modifying URLs","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://com.karwa.WebURL/documentation/WebURL/LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/weburl\/lazilypercentdecodedwithsubstitutions","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"Collection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which percent-decodes elements from its "},{"code":"Source","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on-demand,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and reverses substitutions made by a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/SubstitutionMap","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"title":"LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions","role":"symbol"},"doc://com.karwa.WebURL/documentation/WebURL/WebURL":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"WebURL","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"WebURL","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Uniform Resource Locator (URL) is a universal identifier,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which often describes the location of a resource."}],"url":"\/documentation\/weburl\/weburl","title":"WebURL"},"doc://com.karwa.WebURL/documentation/WebURL/PercentEncodeSet/formEncoding":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/formEncoding","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/weburl\/percentencodeset\/formencoding","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Form-encoding. This encode-set is used to encode "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/url.spec.whatwg.org\/#application\/x-www-form-urlencoded"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"content. It is unique in that it performs substitutions as well as percent-encoding."}],"conformance":{"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Self"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLEncodeSet.FormEncoding"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}]},"title":"formEncoding","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}